  <h1>Smart Clean Privacy Policy</h1>

  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 2026</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Smart Clean is a Google Sheets add-on designed to help users quickly clean and standardize messy spreadsheet data. 
    It provides tools to remove unnecessary spaces and standardize text formatting.
  </p>

  <h2>Information Collection</h2>
  <p>
    Smart Clean does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal or sensitive user data.
  </p>
  <p>
    The add-on only processes the data already present in the user’s Google Sheets and performs cleaning actions directly within the spreadsheet.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Usage</h2>
  <p>Smart Clean only uses spreadsheet data for the following purposes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Removing leading and trailing spaces</li>
    <li>Removing multiple consecutive spaces</li>
    <li>Standardizing text capitalization</li>
    <li>Standardizing email formatting (converting to lowercase)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>All processing occurs within the user's Google Sheets environment.</p>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>
    Smart Clean does not store any user data on external servers or databases.
  </p>
  <p>
    No spreadsheet data is saved, copied, or transmitted outside of Google Sheets.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    Smart Clean does not share any user data with third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <p>
    The add-on may request permission to access Google Sheets in order to perform cleaning operations on the user's spreadsheet data.
  </p>
  <p>
    These permissions are used only to perform the requested functionality.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updates will be reflected on this page.
  </p>

